<section class="cert-infra">
  <div class="section-intro">
    <p class="eyebrow">Certification as Infrastructure</p>
    <h2>How certification becomes institutionally usable</h2>
    <p>
      Certification works because the ARAF system separates methodology,
      assessment, signal, and reliance into distinct functions. This is what allows governance to operate as market infrastructure rather than self-report.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 class="infra-flow-heading" style="position:absolute;left:-9999px;top:auto;width:1px;height:1px;overflow:hidden;">Certification Infrastructure Stages</h2>
  <div class="infra-flow">
    <div class="infra-card">
      <p class="infra-label">Stage 1</p>
      <h3>Standard</h3>
      <p>Defines the methodology</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Six dimensions</li>
        <li>GBI scoring</li>
        <li>Evidence requirements</li>
        <li>Certification thresholds</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="infra-source">Maintained as the published ARAF standard.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="infra-arrow">Defines</div>

    <div class="infra-card">
      <p class="infra-label">Stage 2</p>
      <h3>Assessment</h3>
      <p>Applies the methodology to a deployment</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Dimensional profile</li>
        <li>Multiplier analysis</li>
        <li>Evidence quality</li>
        <li>Remediation roadmap</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="infra-source">Assessment produces the underlying governance record.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="infra-arrow">Produces</div>

    <div class="infra-card">
      <p class="infra-label">Stage 3</p>
      <h3>Certification</h3>
      <p>Issues the institutional signal</p>
      <ul>
        <li>ARAF Assessed</li>
        <li>ARAF Compliant</li>
        <li>ARAF Certified</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="infra-source">Independent accredited assessors issue certification.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="infra-arrow">Enables</div>

    <div class="infra-card">
      <p class="infra-label">Stage 4</p>
      <h3>Institutional Reliance</h3>
      <p>Signal used in decision-making</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Underwriting</li>
        <li>Investment diligence</li>
        <li>Board oversight</li>
        <li>Procurement and review</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="infra-source">Institutions act on the signal without rerunning the full methodology.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p class="infra-caption">
    The standard defines. Assessors evaluate. Certification communicates. Institutions rely. No single actor controls the full chain. That separation is what gives the signal credibility.
  </p>
</section>
